import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    data['height'].plot(kind='bar')
    plt.axhline(y=avg_height, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average height of individuals in the dataset?")
    plt.xlabel("Individuals")
    plt.ylabel("Height")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame, name: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    specific_name_data = data[data['name'] == name]
    plt.hist(specific_name_data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('Age distribution for individuals with the name ' + name)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data, 'John')
chart.show()
